That corrections are difficult for ASR systems is generally explained by the fact that they tend to be hyperarticulatedhigher, louder, longerthan other turns (Wade, Shriberg, and Price 1992; Oviatt et al. 1996; Levow 1998; Bell and Gustafson 1999; Shimojima, et al. 2001; Soltau and Waibel 1998, 2000; Soltau, Metze, and Waibel 2002), where ASR models are not well adapted to handle this special speaking style, although recent studies suggest that ASR systems are becoming less vulnerable to hyperarticulation (Bulyko et al. 2005). 
